Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)¶

1- What is the best source to tweet ?

In [14]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
base_color=sns.color_palette()[0]
sns.countplot(data=df_twitter, x='source', color=base_color)
plt.xticks(rotation=15, size=12)
plt.ylabel("Count", size=12)
plt.xlabel("Source", size=12)
plt.title("Source vs Count", size=12)
plt.legend(["Stage"],fontsize=12);

Observation :¶

Clearly the best way to tweet is by phone

Which type of dog stage are most popupular year from year ?

In [17]:
plt.figure(figsize=(14,8))
count_stage_year=df_twitter[df_twitter.Stage.isin(["doggo","puppo","pupper","floofer"])].groupby(["Stage","year"]).size().reset_index(name='Count')
sns.heatmap(count_stage_year.pivot(index = 'Stage', columns = 'year', values = 'Count'),annot = True,fmt = '.0f',
           cbar_kws={'label': 'Count'})
plt.xlabel('Year',size=12)
plt.ylabel('Stage',size=12);

Observation :¶

Clearly we can see that the pupper is most popular in 2015,2016 and dogggo is most popular in 2017
